summary: An Ordinance providing for the improvement of Fourteenth Avenue South, in the City of Seattle, from Washington Street to Yesler Way, by grading the same, constructing wooden gutters and cross walks and concrete sidewalks, in accordance with Resolution No. 1205 of the City Council of the City of Seattle, and providing for the payment therefor by the mode of "Payment by Bonds," as provided by the laws of the State of Washington and the Charter and Ordinances of the City of Seattle
